 "data": "@startuml DecoyStateQKD\n\nstart\n\n:Alice prepares quantum signals;\nnote right\n Some signals are \"signal states\" (intended for key)\n Others are \"decoy states\" (traps to detect eavesdropping)\nend note\n\n:Alice randomly chooses between signal and decoy states;\nnote right\n Common method: Use different mean photon numbers (μ)\n e.g., signal state: μ = 0.5, decoy states: μ = 0.1, 0\nend note\n\n:Alice encodes each photon using BB84 protocol;\nnote right\n BB84: uses 4 polarization states\n (\"0\" and \"1\" in two bases: rectilinear \"+\" and diagonal \"×\")\nend note\n\n:Alice sends quantum states to Bob;\n\n:Bob measures incoming photons using random bases;\n\n:Alice and Bob announce their basis choices over public channel;\n\n:They discard mismatched basis measurements;\n\n:They sort results by type: signal vs decoy;\n\n:Alice and Bob estimate error rates and detection rates;\nnote right\n For each intensity (μ), compute:\n - \"Q_μ\": gain (detection probability)\n - \"E_μ\": quantum bit error rate (QBER)\nend note\n\n:Check for inconsistencies in decoy statistics;\nnote right\n If Eve is present:\n - Decoy state statistics will differ from expected\n - Use statistical bounds like:\n \"Y_1 ≥ (μ_s Q_d - μ_d Q_s) / (μ_s μ_d (μ_s - μ_d))\"\n where:\n - \"Y_1\": yield of single-photon states\n - \"Q_s\", \"Q_d\": gain of signal/decoy\nend note\n\nif (Eavesdropping detected?) then (Yes)\n :Abort protocol;\n stop\nelse (No)\n :Perform error correction and privacy amplification;\n note right\n Use classical algorithms to:\n - Reconcile errors\n - Remove Eve's potential knowledge\n end note\n\n :Generate final secure key;\n stop\nendif\n\n@enduml\n",
 "format": "svg"

e^(-ημ))\" as overallGain\n\nrectangle \"Calculate E_μQ_μ\\n E_μQ_μ = e₀Y₀ + e_detector(1 - e^(-ημ))\" as EmuQmu\n\nrectangle \"Calculate QBER\\n E_μ = E_μQ_μ / Q_μ\" as QBER\n\ndistance --> channelTrans\nchannelTrans --> totalTrans\ntotalTrans --> overallGain\ntotalTrans --> EmuQmu\noverallGain --> QBER\nEmuQmu --> QBER\n\nnote right of channelTrans\n α: fiber loss coefficient (dB/km)\nend note\n\nnote right of totalTrans\n η_bob: Bob's side efficiency\nend note\n\nnote right of overallGain\n Y₀: background rate\n μ: signal state intensity\nend note\n\nnote right of EmuQmu\n e₀: error rate of background (0.5)\n e_detector: detector error probability\nend note\n\n@enduml","format":"svg"}" id="ji_0P4SmUs5cDvrpFkbA-5"> <mxCell style="shape=image;noLabel=1;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;image=data:image/svg+xml,;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="110" y="130" width="1858.83" height="850" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> </UserObject> </root> </mxGraphModel> </diagram> <diagram id="MRbSu6UfF7LkEqQIwQ4-" name="COWqkd-steps"> <mxGraphModel grid="1" page="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1100" pageHeight="850" math="0" shadow="0"> <root> <mxCell id="0" /> <mxCell id="1" parent="0" /> <UserObject label="" plantUmlData="{"data":"@startuml COW_QKD_Protocol\n\nstart\n\n:Alice prepares weak coherent pulses;\nnote right\n\"Coherent states\" |α⟩| with mean photon number \nmu (typically mu ≈ 0.2 - 0.5)\nend note\n\n:Alice encodes bits using time-bin encoding;\nnote right\nBit 0 → pulse in time slot t₁: (|α⟩, |0⟩)\nBit 1 → pulse in time slot t₂: (|0⟩, |α⟩)\nend note\n\n:Alice randomly inserts decoy states;\nnote right\nDecoy state: (|α⟩, |α⟩)\nUsed for coherence check (no key bits encoded)\nend note\n\n:Send pulses over quantum channel (optical fiber);\n\n:Bob receives incoming pulses;\n\n:Bob uses two detectors;\nnote right\n1. \"Data line\" detector \n→ checks which time slot had the pulse \n→ extracts raw key bits\n2. \"Monitoring line\" detector \n→ interferometer setup \n→ checks coherence of adjacent pulses\nend note\n\n:Bob records detection events and interference results;\n\n:Bob announces detection times over classical channel;\n\n:Alice and Bob sift key;\nnote right\nOnly events with single pulse in time slot\\n\n(i.e., not decoy) are kept\nend note\n\n:Bob uses monitoring results to check visibility;\nnote right\nVisibility V = (I_max - I_min)/(I_max + I_min)\nIf V < threshold, possible eavesdropping detected\nend note\n\nif (Error rate/visibility OK?) then (yes)\n :Proceed to error correction;\n :Perform privacy amplification;\n :Generate final shared key;\nelse (no)\n :Abort protocol;\nend if\n\nstop\n\n@enduml\n","format":"svg"}" id="S0LWE3_DC0QZeREkPPab-2"> <mxCell style="shape=image;noLabel=1;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;image=data:image/svg+xml,;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="80" y="-20" width="721" height="897" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> </UserObject> </root> </mxGraphModel> </diagram> <diagram id="9vwarGnPcaxQvU5HEph1" name="decoystateqkd-skr"> <mxGraphModel grid="1" page="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1100" pageHeight="850" math="0" shadow="0"> <root> <mxCell id="0" /> <mxCell id="1" parent="0" /> <UserObject label="" plantUmlData="{"data":"@startuml\nskinparam backgroundColor white\nskinparam defaultTextAlignment center\nskinparam noteBackgroundColor LightYellow\nskinparam noteBorderColor Gray\n\nstart\n:Inputs:\nDistance, Wavelength, Fiber loss coefficient (α),\nDetector error probability, Background rate (Y₀),\nBob's efficiency (η_bob), Signal state (μ), Decoy states (ν₁, ν₂);\n\n:Calculate channel transmittance:\n\"t_AB = 10^(-(α * distance) / 10)\";\n\n:Calculate total transmittance:\n\"η = t_AB * η_bob\";\n\nfork\n :Calculate overall gain (Q_μ):\n \"Q_μ = Y₀ + (1 - e^(-ημ))\";\n \n :Calculate overall QBER (E_μ):\n \"E_μQ_μ = e₀Y₀ + e_detector(1 - e^(-ημ))\"\n \"E_μ = E_μQ_μ / Q_μ\";\nfork again\n :Calculate decoy state gains:\n \"Q_ν₁ = Y₀ + (1 - e^(-ην₁))\"\n \"Q_ν₂ = Y₀ + (1 - e^(-ην₂))\";\n \n :Calculate decoy state QBERs:\n \"E_ν₁ = (e₀Y₀ + e_detector(1 - e^(-ην₁))) / Q_ν₁\"\n \"E_ν₂ = (e₀Y₀ + e_detector(1 - e^(-ην₂))) / Q_ν₂\";\nend fork\n\n:Estimate Y₀ lower bound:\n\"Y₀_L = max((ν₁Q_ν₂e^ν₂ - ν₂Q_ν₁e^ν₁)/(ν₁-ν₂), 0)\";\n\n:Estimate Y₁ lower bound:\n\"Y₁_L = (μ/denominator) * numerator\"\nwhere:\n\"numerator = Q_ν₁e^ν₁ - Q_ν₂e^ν₂ - ((ν₁²-ν₂²)/μ²)(Q_μe^μ-Y₀_L)\"\n\"denominator = μν₁ - μν₂ - ν₁² + ν₂²\";\n\n:Calculate Q₁ lower bound:\n\"Q₁_L = Y₁_L * μ * e^(-μ)\";\n\n:Calculate e₁ upper bound:\n\"e₁_U = (E_ν₁Q_ν₁e^ν₁ - E_ν₂Q_ν₂e^ν₂)/((ν₁-ν₂)Y₁_L)\";\n\n:Calculate binary Shannon entropy:\n\"H₂(x) = -x * log₂(x) - (1-x) * log₂(1-x)\";\n\n:Calculate secure key rate:\n\"R = q * (-Q_μ * f * H₂(E_μ) + Q₁_L * (1 - H₂(e₁_U))) * rep_rate\";\n\n:Return max(0, R);\n\nstop\n@enduml","format":"svg"}" id="mm1GpHyD5PyPsM06uP5C-3"> <mxCell style="shape=image;noLabel=1;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;image=data:image/svg+xml,;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="-170" y="-310" width="654" height="1006" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> </UserObject> </root> </mxGraphModel> </diagram> <diagram id="_VjiAg2k0-7Q8zoSwMcT" name="COWqkd-qber"> <mxGraphModel grid="1" page="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1100" pageHeight="850" math="0" shadow="0"> <root> <mxCell id="0" /> <mxCell id="1" parent="0" /> <UserObject label="" plantUmlData="{

 "data": "@startuml\nstart\n\n:Alice prepares a train of weak coherent light pulses;\nnote right\n Each pulse has an average photon number less than 1 \n (e.g., \"μ\" ≈ 0.1 photons per pulse)\nend note\n\n:Alice encodes each pulse with a random phase shift;\nnote right\n Phase shift \"φ_i\" ∈ {\"0\", \"π\"}\n The actual information is in the phase difference:\n \"Δφ_i = φ_i - φ_(i-1)\" mod \"2π\"\nend note\n\n:Alice sends the pulse train to Bob over a quantum channel;\n\n:Bob uses a Mach-Zehnder interferometer;\nnote right\n Interferometer compares pulse \"i\" and pulse \"i-1\"\n Output depends on \"Δφ_i\":\n If \"Δφ_i = 0\", detector D0 clicks\n If \"Δφ_i = π\", detector D1 clicks\nend note\n\nif (Bob detects a photon?) then (yes)\n :Bob records the detector click and time;\n :Bob infers \"Δφ_i\" based on the detector;\nelse (no)\n :No information recorded;\nendif\n\n:Bob sends detection times (but not phase info) to Alice;\n\n:Alice and Bob keep only bits where Bob got a click;\nnote right\n This forms the raw key based on phase differences\nend note\n\n:Alice and Bob perform error correction and privacy amplification;\nnote right\n They remove errors and reduce Eve's information \n Final result is a shared secret key\nend note\n\nstop\n@enduml\n",

 "data": "@startuml\nskinparam defaultTextAlignment center\n\nstart\n:Input Parameters;\nnote right\n nem = Number of blocks\n mu = Mean photon number\n ebit = Bit error rate\n eta_det = Detector efficiency\n dark_count = Dark count probability\n alpha = Fiber loss coefficient\n distance = Channel distance\n delta_bs1, delta_bs2 = BS transmittance deviations\n t_prob = Code event selection probability\n repetition_rate = Pulse repetition rate\nend note\n\n:Calculate Channel Properties;\nnote right\n \"eta_ch = 10^(-alpha * distance / 10)\"\n \"eta = eta_ch * eta_det\"\nend note\n\n:Calculate Lambda Factor;\nnote right\n \"term1 = 1 - (1 - eta1) * eta2\"\n \"term2 = sqrt((term1)^2 - 4 * eta1 * (1 - eta1) * (1 - eta2)^2)\"\n \"lambda = (term1 + term2) / (2 * (1 - eta1) * (1 - eta2)^2)\"\nend note\n\nif (Is mu explicitly provided?) then (yes)\n :Mu Analysis Mode;\n \n :Calculate Yields and Gains;\n note right\n \"Y[0] = dark_count\"\n \"Y[n>0] = 1 - (1 - eta)^n\"\n \"gain[n] = p_n * Y[n]\"\n \"p_n = exp(-3*mu) * (3*mu)^n / n!\"\n \"Q = sum(gain[n])\"\n end note\n \n :Calculate Phase Error Rate;\n note right\n \"e_phase = (gain[0] * 0.5 + gain[1] * e1 + sum(gain[n>=2] * 0.5)) / Q\"\n end note\n \n :Calculate Secret Fraction;\n note right\n \"r = max(0, gain[1]/Q * (1 - h(e_phase)) - h(ebit))\"\n \"where h(p) = -p*log2(p) - (1-p)*log2(1-p)\"\n end note\n \n :Calculate SKR;\n note right\n \"R = r * Q\"\n end note\n\nelse (no)\n :Distance Analysis Mode;\n \n :Calculate Detection Rate;\n note right\n \"Q = 2 * eta * mu * exp(-2 * eta * mu)\"\n end note\n \n :Calculate Photon Number Probabilities;\n note right\n \"q1 = exp(-3*mu) * (3*mu)^1 / 1!\"\n \"q2 = exp(-3*mu) * (3*mu)^2 / 2!\"\n \"q3 = exp(-3*mu) * (3*mu)^3 / 3!\"\n end note\n \n :Calculate Upper Bound on Phase Error Rate;\n note right\n \"e_U_ph = (lambda_factor * (ebit + sqrt(q1 * q3) / Q + 2 * delta_bs2) + q2 / Q)\"\n end note\n \n :Calculate Secret Key Length;\n note right\n \"Ncode = t_prob * nem * Q\"\n \"NEC = Ncode * h(ebit)\"\n \"NPA = Ncode * h(e_U_ph)\"\n \"ell = Ncode - NPA - NEC\"\n end note\n \n :Calculate SKR;\n note right\n \"R = ell / (3 * nem)\"\n end note\nendif\n\n:Convert to bits per second;\nnote right\n \"R_bps = R * repetition_rate\"\nend note\n\n:Output SKR;\nnote right\n \"Final Secret Key Rate in bits per second\"\nend note\n\nstop\n@enduml",

probability:\np_detect_total = 2 * (sifted key rate)\n(sifted key rate = raw key rate * 0.5);\n\n:Calculate QBER:\nQBER(%) = (p_error / p_detect_total) * 100;\n\nstop\n@enduml\n","format":"svg"}"
